Log-Any-Adapter-Term

Adapter for Log::Any that logs to the terminal. Includes color output for
interactive terminals.


INSTALLATION

To install from CPAN:

   sudo cpan Log::Any::Adapter::Term

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Log::Any::Adapter::Term

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Log-Any-Adapter-Term

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Log-Any-Adapter-Term

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Log-Any-Adapter-Term

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Log-Any-Adapter-Term/


